This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with optimizing convolutional neural networks (CNNs) which are commonly used in computer vision tasks. It is also likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories as it involves training a dynamic network that can modify its objective at inference time. Additionally, it may belong to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category as it deals with optimizing the performance of neural networks. Finally, it may belong to the software engineering (cs.SD) sub-category as it involves developing a fast and interactive solution for modifying the network in real-time.
